#### Textbook

I continue to compile a series of Jupyter notebooks that I use as instructional materials using Sphinx, hosting the files on Readthedocs.  You can also download the notebooks directly from the github repository.  Further, feel free to fork the website repository and adjust the notebooks to create your own course text.

* [Full Text on Readthedocs](http://calculus-notes.readthedocs.io/en/latest/)
* [Jupyter notebooks on github](https://github.com/jfkoehler/calc_docs/tree/master/source)

